      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i want to dig a bit deeper into the risk side. some people say the 'existential risk' argument is actually just a way for big companies to pull the ladder up behind them through regulation, while others say it's a mathematical certainty that we'll lose control. in your view, is the risk of an existential catastrophe a settled scientific concern or is it more of a speculative hypothesis?",
