      "content": "i hear that, but when you say \"the majority of the scientific community views it as a plausible risk,\" that feels like it downplays how urgent the warnings are from people like Geoffrey Hinton or Yoshua Bengio. if the most brilliant people in the field are saying we need to slow down because we might lose control of a superintelligence, isn't it more \"responsible\" to treat it as a likely crisis rather than just a \"plausible\" debate? isn't treating them as just one side of a debate basically ignoring the gravity of the situation?",
